From a8b29ddc0d9098e42aa3347e5f8a74546a328dcb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shreedhar Parande <sparande@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 4 Sep 2025 15:10:34 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:hostapd: Avoid Premature Key Deletion
 Before Deauth Transmission

Currently, the AP sends a Disassociation frame to an
MFP enabled inactive STA and schedules a Deauthentication
frame after ap_max_inactivity seconds. However, keys are deleted
during Disassociation itself, resulting in transmission of
an unencrypted Deauthentication frame to the MFP enabled
inactive STA.

As per IEEE P802.11-REVme/D7.0, August 2024,
Section 12.6.17 “Protection of robust Management frames”:
If management frame protection is negotiated for the link,
a STA shall not transmit unprotected individually addressed
Deauthentication frames and shall discard such frames.

To fix this, avoid key deletion during
MLME-DISASSOCIATE.indication if a Deauth timer is
scheduled. Key deletion already occurs during
MLME-DEAUTH.indication. This ensures the Deauth frame
is encrypted as expected.

Patch-work: None
Patch-dependency: None
Internal-review: [PATCH v4] hostapd: Avoid Premature Key Deletion Before Deauth Transmission

Signed-off-by: Shreedhar Parande <sparande@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/ap_mlme.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/ap/ap_mlme.c b/src/ap/ap_mlme.c
index 309e69a..2b85dc2 100644
--- a/src/ap/ap_mlme.c
+++ b/src/ap/ap_mlme.c
@@ -165,6 +165,15 @@ void mlme_disassociate_indication(struct hostapd_data *hapd,
 		       HOSTAPD_LEVEL_DEBUG,
 		       "MLME-DISASSOCIATE.indication(" MACSTR ", %d)",
 		       MAC2STR(sta->addr), reason_code);
+
+	/* Encryption keys must be retained for PMF-enabled STA
+	 * to allow secure DEAUTH transmission as per IEEE P802.11-REVme/D7.0,
+	 * Section 12.6.17.
+	 */
+	if (sta->flags & WLAN_STA_MFP &&
+	    sta->timeout_next == STA_DEAUTH)
+		return;
+
 	mlme_deletekeys_request(hapd, sta);
 }
 
